<paragraph id="8BE3B60599C3FF7801D8FD6AFAF9FBEA" blockId="136.[718,1304,665,1091]" lastBlockId="136.[98,1303,1098,3333]" pageId="136" pageNumber="751">
There is considerable geographic variation in this wide-ranging species, and overforty subspecies have been described. Many of these are considered not well founded, butthis speciesis in need of taxonomic revision. Intermediate variations are often seen where the ranges of two subspecies meet. Eleven subspecies are recognized here; a twelfth subspecies (currently undescribed) may inhabit the higher elevations of 
<collectingRegion id="499878E799C3FF78006EFBC8FB6EFBEA" box="[888,1155,1098,1131]" country="Tanzania" name="Kilimanjaro" pageId="136" pageNumber="751">Mount Kilimanjaro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34BF69599C3FF780787FBC8FAFDFBEA" box="[1169,1296,1098,1131]" name="Tanzania" pageId="136" pageNumber="751">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
